The paper proposes a new approach to boosting for multi-class classification problems, which is a common topic in machine learning and falls under the category of "Learning" (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of regularization to promote group sparsity and feature sharing, which are topics related to "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) and "Computer Vision" (cs.CV). The experiments conducted in the paper involve various datasets, indicating a focus on "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS) and "Social and Information Networks" (cs.SI) for testing and evaluation.
